doc.after: Seattle's climate is usually described as oceanic or temperate marine, with cool, wet winters and warm, relatively dry summers. Like much of the Pacific Northwest, according to the KÃ¶ppen climate classification it has a warm-summer Mediterranean climate (Csb).[66] Other climate classification systems, such as Trewartha, place it firmly in the Oceanic zone (Do), like much of Western Europe.[67] The city and environs are part of USDA hardiness zone 8b, with isolated coastal pockets falling under 9a.[68]
